Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.05,0:00:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H00ffff&\fnRockwell}Improved By: FidelPerez{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\b1\c&Hffff00&\fnRockwell}Sub Upload Date: August 4, 2018{\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.53,0:00:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.11,0:00:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.86,0:00:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}KEVIN FEIGE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}There is just something\Nawesome about seeing these{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.08,0:00:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,different franchise heroes interacting\Nwith each other for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.33,0:00:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}BANNER:{\c}{\fn\b0} Who are you?\N- Natasha Romanoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.00,0:00:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The notion of seeing characters who\Nyou've grown to love in their own movies
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}walking into another movie\Nfor the first time,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.72,0:00:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there is just something\Nthat is satisfying.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.18,0:00:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ROARING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.39,0:00:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We haven't really seen that\Nsince the first Avengers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.06,0:00:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Avengers: Age of Ultron\Nintroduced some new characters
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.14,0:00:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}within the body of that film.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.61,0:00:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Captain America: Civil War\Nintroduced Black Panther and Spider-Man.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.15,0:00:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.23,0:00:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, here we are years later...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.61,0:00:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(WAKANDANS CHANTING IN XHOSA){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.15,0:00:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...doing Infinity War.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.45,0:01:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ALL EXCLAIMS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.96,0:01:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}ROCKET:{\c}{\fn\b0} Wipers! Wipers!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.83,0:01:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it Off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.79,0:01:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ALL GASPS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How the hell is this dude\Nstill alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.88,0:01:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He is not a dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.97,0:01:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.59,0:01:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This... This is a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.30,0:01:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A handsome, muscular man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.93,0:01:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm muscular.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.68,0:01:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're doing something\Nthe fans have wanted from day one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.73,0:01:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.40,0:01:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since the very beginning of getting\Nthe job as Drax in Guardians,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.74,0:01:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really wishing that\Nthe worlds would collide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.70,0:01:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We like to combine things that\Ndon't seem like they belong together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.62,0:01:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel your pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.70,0:01:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel your pain as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The exciting aspect\Nof the film{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.71,0:01:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is that we're gonna take\Nall of these characters{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.37,0:01:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from different franchises\Nin the Marvel Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're gonna put them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.63,0:01:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tony Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.71,0:01:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Doctor Stephen Strange.\NI need you to come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.17,0:01:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, you giving out\Ntickets to something?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.14,0:02:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Strange Alchemy" is a phrase that\Nwe came up with in the writers' room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.68,0:02:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"Which characters can we put together\Nthat audiences are excited to see?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.94,0:02:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your job exactly?\NBesides making balloon animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.31,0:02:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Protecting your reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.57,0:02:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"How do you combine all these different\Ntones, all these different characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.82,0:02:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"and how do we balance it?"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.11,0:02:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is it that they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Kick names, take ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.74,0:02:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.08,0:02:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}That's gonna create\Nthe most spark{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.58,0:02:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because conflict between heroes\Ncan be entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.21,0:02:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing?\N- Taking your pod.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.37,0:02:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(PETER CLEARS THROAT){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.79,0:02:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(IN DEEP VOICE){\c}{\fn\b0}\NNo, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.88,0:02:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You will not be taking\Nour pod today, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.88,0:02:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you making\Nyour voice deeper?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.26,0:02:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We had the opportunity\Nto bring all of the Marvel Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,practically together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.56,0:02:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}RHODES:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}You guys...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,really look like crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.06,0:02:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}TRAN:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}I think those small little\Ncharacter moments{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,are what makes\NMarvel movies so special.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.15,0:02:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GROWLS){\c}{\fn\b0}\N- Where's your guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.65,0:02:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GRUNTING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:02:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dude, you're embarrassing me\Nin front of the wizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.03,0:03:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}T'CHALLA:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}Today, we don't fight\Nfor one life,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we fight for all of them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}So, the greatest test that\Nthese characters will ever face,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.13,0:03:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,they can barely face it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.63,0:03:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}DR. STRANGE:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}We're in the endgame now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.63,0:03:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We are embarking on something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.68,0:03:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that is much bigger than\Nwe've ever embarked on before.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,On its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.77,0:03:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a collaborative thing\Nwhere you've got
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that many people pooling\Ntheir talent together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.44,0:03:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's really something to enjoy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.65,0:03:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- I am Spider-Man.\N- Dr. Strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.82,0:03:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There was sort of a camaraderie\Nbetween us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.99,0:03:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They all make each other\Nbetter in the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.78,0:03:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}PETER:{\c}{\fn\b0} Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.79,0:03:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the Avengers, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}THANOS:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The end is near.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.46,0:03:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's never been\Nanything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.08,0:03:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.29,0:03:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}FEIGE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}It's fun putting people{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:04:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who have no business\Nbeing on the same planet together...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.30,0:04:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- This is a friend of mine.\N- {\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GRUNTING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.64,0:04:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...much less,\Nthe same room together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.26,0:04:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Groot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.89,0:04:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Steve Rogers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}FEIGE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The amount of actors\Nin this film is staggering.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.02,0:04:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- How much for the gun?\N- Not for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. How much for the arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.32,0:04:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look around.\NIt's like, "Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"There's all this potential."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.61,0:04:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for standing with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.62,0:04:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knows this has all been\Nleading to something. Well, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SHOUTS IN XHOSA){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody wants the characters\Nuniting for a big battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.34,0:04:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}PROXIMA MIDNIGHT:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}You'll die alone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}BLACK WIDOW:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}She's not alone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.55,0:04:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we make these movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That, to us, is the fun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.56,0:04:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an Avenger now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wakanda forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.96,0:05:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}GAMORA:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The entire time I knew him,\Nhe only ever had one goal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.71,0:05:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To bring balance to the universe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.01,0:05:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by wiping out half of all life.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.47,0:05:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He kills people planet by planet,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}massacre by massacre.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.77,0:05:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me his name again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.48,0:05:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.23,0:05:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanos has been lurking in the shadows\Nof our universe
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}since Avengers one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We see a glimpse of him\Nin Guardians of the Galaxy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.46,0:05:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I will bathe the star ways\Nin your blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.17,0:06:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}FEIGE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}We see a tiny glimpse of him\Nat the end of Age of Ultron.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.00,0:06:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He has had his hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in every action that has occurred\Non a grand level in the MCU,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.93,0:06:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}all surrounding his desire\Nto obtain these Infinity Stones.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone has been playing an intricate\Ngame and has made pawns of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.94,0:06:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}GAMORA:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}If he gets\Nall the Infinity Stones,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he can wipe out half\Nthe universe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with the snap of his fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.32,0:06:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.87,0:06:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Stones are spread out\Nthroughout the franchises.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.46,0:06:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We're building every one of them\Ninto this epic, colossal event.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}STARK:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}So, this is it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.59,0:06:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all been leading to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.93,0:06:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Josh Brolin is bringing\Na new iconic villain to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanos is a very complex character.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.56,0:07:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What he's doing, from his point of view,\Nis a very positive thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.78,0:07:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's basically an eco-terrorist,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.36,0:07:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wants to eliminate 50% of\Nthe universe to save the other 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.29,0:07:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to tell a story\Nabout a character
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.83,0:07:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with a really complex\Nand empathetic interior life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And there's not a lot of actors\Nthat can give you both of those things.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.17,0:07:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}D'ESPOSITO:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}Josh Brolin brings\Na reality to the character.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's wearing that mocap suit,\Nhe's wearing motion capture cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.56,0:07:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The performance is coming through,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.02,0:07:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}not only in his gestures, in his face,\Nbut in his eyes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}VICTORIA ALONSO:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}There's about 2,900\Nvisual effects shots in the movie.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.77,0:07:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We wanted to make it\Nas photographic as possible.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.99,0:07:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that\Nthat's the most important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.16,0:07:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SCREAMING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:07:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}MANTIS:{\c}{\fn\b0} What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.46,0:08:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}GAMORA:{\c}{\fn\b0}\NDeath follows him like a shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.92,0:08:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's who Thanos is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to know\Na great deal about Thanos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.76,0:08:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Gamora is the daughter\Nof Thanos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Infinity War reveals\Nthis whole new world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.73,0:08:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that Nebula and Gamora\Nhave been running away from for years.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}GAMORA:{\c}{\fn\b0} Nebula!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}THANOS:{\c}{\fn\b0} Some time ago, your sister\Nsnuck aboard this ship to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I brought her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,His relationship with Gamora,\Nit's quite emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.46,0:08:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SCREAMING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.46,0:08:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I ignored my destiny once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.30,0:08:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot do that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.80,0:08:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Even for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.97,0:09:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}D'ESPOSITO:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}What makes Thanos\Nso great is his conviction.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.02,0:09:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the only solution.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.39,0:09:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's seen it firsthand\Non his planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.94,0:09:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}THANOS:{\c}{\fn\b0}\NTitan was like most planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.36,0:09:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we faced extinction,\NI offered a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Genocide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.24,0:09:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What I predicted came to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.99,0:09:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, you're a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.33,0:09:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.34,0:09:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tony knows just by the way that\NBruce Banner describes Thanos,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.97,0:09:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a different game now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.09,0:09:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}BANNER:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}He sent Loki.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.30,0:09:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack on New York,\Nthat's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He has the biggest army in the universe,\Nand he is not gonna stop.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just his sheer force is something
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that none of the Avengers\Nhas ever encountered before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.36,0:09:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanos has been\Ninside my head for six years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say we take the fight to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.24,0:10:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}Heroes are only\Nas good as their villain,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but if the Avengers\Nwere built for anything,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.75,0:10:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it's for stopping Thanos\Nfrom completing his goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.68,0:10:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}THANOS:{\c}{\fn\b0} Fun really isn't something one\Nconsiders when balancing the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but this does put\Na smile on my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.89,0:10:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.98,0:10:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GRUNTS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.07,0:10:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanos is the greatest villain
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in the history\Nof Marvel Cinematic Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SCREAMS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The hardest choices require\Nthe strongest wills.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you'll find our will\Nequal to yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SCREAMS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.35,0:11:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine if our heroes all lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.72,0:11:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have gone\Nfor the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.85,0:11:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.94,0:11:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Marvel Cinematic Universe\Nwill never be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.86,0:11:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.37,0:11:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.00,0:11:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What did it cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.88,0:11:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Avengers {\i1}3{\i0} is by far and away\Nthe most intense of all three films.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.58,0:12:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(PEOPLE SCREAMING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.79,0:12:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of the reason why we were drawn\Nto tell the story of {\i1}Civil{\i0} War
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and one of the reasons why\Nwe thought{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.34,0:12:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it was such a great place\Nto leave the Avengers divided{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was because we knew the greatest threat\Nthey would ever face
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}would be coming in Thanos.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.64,0:12:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For storytellers, you want your heroes\Nto be at their lowest point{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.81,0:12:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when they meet\Ntheir worst threat.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The hardest choices require\Nthe strongest wills.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.57,0:12:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you'll find our will\Nequal to yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.37,0:12:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}This film\Nwas taking all the characters{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.29,0:12:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from all the different franchises{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.75,0:12:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and putting them together in one movie\Nfor the first time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.96,0:12:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about as massive a production\Nas you could mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.63,0:12:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We need a plan. If all we come at him\Nwith is plucky attitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't call us plucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.84,0:13:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.59,0:13:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in production all year\Non {\i1}Infinity{\i0} War.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.97,0:13:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the largest global shoot\Nwe've ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.47,0:13:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Joe and Anthony have the stamina\Nto do two films, back-to-back.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.73,0:13:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Moving on to a clean pass.\N- Okay, back to the other set.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.19,0:13:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Something this big\Nisn't daunting to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.07,0:13:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And they're the perfect combination\Nof structure and freedom.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Do what you want to do\Non this first take,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.36,0:13:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll start\Nto tweak it from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.78,0:13:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Russos elevated the franchise,\Neven past its inception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.79,0:13:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ALL LAUGHING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.13,0:13:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.25,0:13:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent a lot of time with\NJoe and Anthony, Markus and McFeely
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}creating storylines that really allow\Nthese characters their moments.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Action!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.39,0:13:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If he gets his hands\Non all six stones, Tony...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.43,0:13:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He could destroy life\Non a scale hitherto undreamt of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.89,0:13:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you seriously just say\N"hitherto undreamt of"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.23,0:13:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You really look at\Nhow all the characters interweave
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.69,0:13:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}into the main arc.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}ANTHONY:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The connective tissue that\Npulls our entire MCU together{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.32,0:14:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is the fact that the Stones are\Nspread out throughout the franchises.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.61,0:14:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The exciting aspect\Nof the film is that{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.83,0:14:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to take\Nall of these characters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.70,0:14:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from different franchises\Nin the Marvel Universe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.87,0:14:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're going to put them together\Nto stop Thanos from completing his goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.33,0:14:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes months\Nto plan sequences like Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.47,0:14:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Titan, we shot that exclusively\Non a sound stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.73,0:14:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}DAN DeLEEUW:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}Beautiful set built by Charlie Wood,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}our production designer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.44,0:14:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's green screen\Nin the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.61,0:14:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All that extension will be from plates\Nthat we went to Chile and shot.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}VICTORIA ALONSO:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}This entire movie is one big CG scene.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The environment is CG,\Nthe weapons are CG,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.86,0:14:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}every shot is dense in layers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We were pushing colors\Nin both locations,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.25,0:14:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}more green and yellows in Wakanda,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.58,0:15:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and more orange hues\Nand red hues in Titan,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could distinguish the two\Nas you're intercutting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a constant challenge to see,\Nhow do we keep this photographic enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.26,0:15:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We wanted to have that apocalyptic look\Nthat both Joe and Anthony wanted.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.35,0:15:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That it was the end of an era.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.81,0:15:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Heroes are only as good\Nas their villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.36,0:15:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And we spent a lot of time\Nand energy on this one{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.23,0:15:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}making sure that Thanos was\Nthe most intense and the best villain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.49,0:15:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that the Marvel Universe has seen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.32,0:15:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We had had an initial meeting,\Nme and the Russos,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it was incredibly helpful.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.83,0:15:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like they cared deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.75,0:15:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}MATT AITKENI:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}Thanos is entirely digital,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.25,0:15:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so we have Josh Brolin\Nperforming him on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}SWEN GILLBERG:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}We record\Nall the positions of all their joints,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.51,0:15:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and we record their motion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.42,0:15:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We've dotted up his face, and basically\Nthose two cameras give us
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.76,0:15:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a {\i1}three-dimensional solid of his face\Nin very fine detail.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.47,0:15:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The performance is coming through,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.68,0:16:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}not only in his gestures\Nand in his face, but in his eyes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're much more of a Thanos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.86,0:16:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I take it the Maw is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.24,0:16:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This day extracts a heavy toll.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The battle between\NThanos and Dr. Strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.78,0:16:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that was all previz.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.33,0:16:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And the way\Nwe work through that{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.58,0:16:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is probably that sequence was twice\Nas long as it ended up in the movie,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.54,0:16:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so we shrunk it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we agree\Non what that sequence is,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.71,0:16:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the only element that is missing\Nfrom a sequence like that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.17,0:16:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is Benedict Cumberbatch.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll then go shoot\NBenedict Cumberbatch,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.84,0:16:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but everything else is\Nalready turned over to the VFX vendors,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.26,0:16:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so they can get to work\Non Thanos' side of it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.64,0:16:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and everything else around\NDr. Strange.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.02,0:16:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're full of tricks, wizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.40,0:16:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Action sequences are very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.61,0:16:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GRUNTS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Every action sequence is used\Nto illuminate character,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,who the character is,\Nwhat they're made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You never once used\Nyour greatest weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.87,0:17:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(STRAINING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.42,0:17:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.84,0:17:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Those battles usually start with\Neither the stunt team or the VFX team.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.47,0:17:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.76,0:17:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We owe it to Sam Hargrave to create\Nthese amazing stunts for Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.73,0:17:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a room full of movie stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got three franchise-carrying\Nactors here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.73,0:17:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our first day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we are in Pinewood in Atlanta,\Nand it's actually pretty unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.41,0:17:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can actually engage in this\Ncollaborative, creative conversation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about what should this look like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.96,0:17:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We would show them\Nour previz material
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,just to let them know, like,\Nthese are the certain things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.21,0:17:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that you would be working with\Nto get to this final product.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.34,0:17:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to look awesome\Nwhen Chris does it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.80,0:17:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ALL CHUCKLES){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}Every character,\Nevery hero involved{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.60,0:18:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has to use the highest level\Nof their power
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.23,0:18:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,just to stay on the battlefield\Nwith him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.36,0:18:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The big two. Thanos versus Iron Man.\NThis is the showdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.73,0:18:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what the whole movie's\Nleading up to right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.20,0:18:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got Robert Downey, Jr.,\NJosh Brolin,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,going hand-to-hand, right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}THANOS:{\c}{\fn\b0} Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.79,0:18:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.87,0:18:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I know your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It is much like mine,\Ncursed with knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.29,0:18:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My only curse is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Iron Man has been battling\Nfor six years now
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.05,0:18:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the shadow of Thanos.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.26,0:18:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He has been waiting\Nfor this moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.05,0:18:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(PANTING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All that for a drop of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.56,0:18:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GASPS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.16,0:19:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew we were going\Nto a place in the story
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.87,0:19:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that audiences wouldn't expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I drive him back\Nlike this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,pin him down like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.54,0:19:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes or no?\N- Yeah, I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was our intent in this movie\Nto play against your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}MAN:{\c}{\fn\b0} Action!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.51,0:19:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GROANING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.59,0:19:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have my respect, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.01,0:19:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm done, half of humanity\Nwill still be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.77,0:19:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(G ROANS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.15,0:19:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The movie sort of keeps twisting\Nat the end there
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.40,0:19:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in ways that you can't believe\Nthat it's going one step beyond,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the fate\Nof our characters
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.07,0:19:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fate of the universe\Nare still at play.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.36,0:19:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Stark? I don't feel so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.45,0:19:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter Parker uses all of the strength\Nthat he has as a hero
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.08,0:19:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to fight against disappearing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.66,0:19:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all right.\NYou're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}It allows him to last longer\Nthan some of the others.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.71,0:20:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotional experience\Nthat the characters are going through
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as they experience that\Nis where the power lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.76,0:20:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I don't want to go.\NI don't want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}DOWNEY JR:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The Russos realized how\Nyou had to bring it to the next level{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.14,0:20:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and also have it\Nhave a great surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SOFTLY){\c}{\fn\b0} I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.11,0:20:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}D'ESPOSITO:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}Never seen\Nour Avengers really lose,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.24,0:20:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and they lost, and it's quite\Nemotional to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.99,0:20:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.58,0:20:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}MCFEELY:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}It's a big, epic movie,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.87,0:20:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and stakes are high,\Nwith characters that, hopefully,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.17,0:20:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}because since 2008\Nyou started to love these people,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.71,0:20:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you really care about.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the grand experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we just lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarely, especially in Avengers {\i1}3,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.56,0:20:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,do commercial movies go to the place\Nthat this film goes to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:20:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Quill?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.99,0:21:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.82,0:21:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}DR. STRANGE:{\c}{\fn\b0}\NWe're in the endgame now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You murdered half the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A small price to pay for salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.28,0:21:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}JOE RUSSO:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The level of ambition\Nwith Avengers 3 is unprecedented.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.45,0:21:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was the reason\Nthat we wanted to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.91,0:21:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}ROBERT DOWNEY JR:{\c}{\fn\b0}\NInfinity War is {\i1}nuts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty in executing it\Nwas so well thought out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.91,0:21:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of things have to\Nkind of fit into place,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.17,0:21:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and that's just a tricky target to hit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.88,0:22:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is D-Day, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}People don't understand what\Nthey're walking into with this movie.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.42,0:22:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is not going to end well\Nfor a lot of people.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}KAREN GILLAN:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}The stakes are very high,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.30,0:22:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we are going\Nto say goodbye to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.35,0:22:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The whole thing\Nis just gigantic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.93,0:22:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the experience of working\Nwith Markus and McFeely on {\i1}Civil{\i0} War,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.85,0:22:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we knew that\Nthere was a culmination coming.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.19,0:22:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But how do you combine\Nall these different tones,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.27,0:22:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}all these different characters?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.52,0:22:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the way\Nwe end up balancing it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.32,0:22:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is we always try to ground it in\Nan emotional truth for the character.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.16,0:22:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If we take out the stone...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.95,0:22:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,there's still a whole lot\Nof Vision left.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.58,0:22:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the best parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.45,0:22:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.37,0:22:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not me, not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.63,0:22:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I know somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like there's a lot of substance\Nbehind them coming to Wakanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.47,0:22:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've seen Wakanda\Nas a powerful nation,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.97,0:22:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but we've also seen it\Nhave to battle with itself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.68,0:22:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And so being a part of this major moment\Nfor the Avengers,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.52,0:22:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it felt like very significant\Nstorylines merging.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.40,0:23:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}ROGERS:{\c}{\fn\b0} Seems like I'm always\Nthanking you for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.86,0:23:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the men really respect each\Nother and have similar moral compasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.94,0:23:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and are eager to be there\Nwhen the other person's in need.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.07,0:23:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He just happens to have\Na whole army.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.16,0:23:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.37,0:23:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,On its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.04,0:23:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,For our 19th movie,\Nten years in the making,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.37,0:23:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the Russo brothers really wanted\Nto create this big, epic battle{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that was worth the biggest,\Nbaddest villain and his army.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.26,0:23:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the most physically challenging\Nthing that we've ever clone
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.55,0:23:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was execute that Wakanda sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.72,0:23:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The scope is gigantic\Non this movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it's the largest battle\Nthat we've ever done.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for standing with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.85,0:23:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SPEAKS XHOSA){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.40,0:23:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.77,0:23:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We shot Wakanda in a practical location.\NIt was a big ranch in Georgia
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.44,0:23:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that we transformed\Ninto the fields of Wakanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.16,0:23:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}DAN DeLEEUW:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}Working with the Russo brothers,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.24,0:23:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the main theme is, they want to keep\Neverything grounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.16,0:23:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So art department's gone in\Nand basically built a river{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.33,0:24:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and has dressed in a lot of trees\Nthat are more indigenous to Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.42,0:24:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie Wood and his art department\Nactually carved an artificial river
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.13,0:24:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}through the center\Nof this field,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.88,0:24:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and we had a gigantic pump that could\Ndo like 30,000 gallons a minute.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.63,0:24:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very elaborate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.18,0:24:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We want the scope to be huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.93,0:24:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So what we're doing is, we're using\Na set as the center of the war scene,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.18,0:24:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and then anything you see off\Nin the distance we're actually replacing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.77,0:24:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with plates and textures\Nfrom Africa itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.14,0:24:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We actually had to work in tandem\Nwith Ryan Coogler.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.23,0:24:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He and his team had maps of Wakanda.\NThat was very helpful to us,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.32,0:24:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so that we could look at\Nwhere we wanted to place the battle,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.90,0:24:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,understand strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.40,0:24:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's literally\Nlike doing a Jenga puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.70,0:24:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(CHANTING IN XHOSA){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.49,0:24:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the Russos work,\Nthey're willing to try different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.75,0:24:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a lot of input, and we could\Nshare how we would express ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.38,0:24:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what war cries we use\Nas Wakandans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.38,0:24:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We have another one\Nthat's more aggressive
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.38,0:24:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.72,0:24:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's mie effa,\Nwhich means "win them."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.43,0:24:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sie effa means "separate them."\NAnd theyjust go... {\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GRUNTING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.31,0:24:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the actors involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.64,0:25:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course they know their characters\Nbetter than anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.77,0:25:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They have great input.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.77,0:25:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say it, it's the greatest\N"Wakanda forever" you've ever said,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.56,0:25:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because this could be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.82,0:25:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it became sort of the cadence\Nof the whole set.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.57,0:25:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,People walking around saying,\N"Wakanda forever!"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.99,0:25:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Wakanda forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.49,0:25:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ALL SHOUTING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.70,0:25:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna clash the Wakandan army\Nwith the Outriders.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.62,0:25:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Where good meets evil,\Nand they battle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.13,0:25:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really amazing to see\Nthe vastness of the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.30,0:25:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It made sense that this is the sort of\Nbattle that could end the universe.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.38,0:25:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You definitely kind of catch yourself\Nlooking around
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.34,0:25:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and you have goosebumps.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.30,0:25:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got the Wakandan army,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.85,0:25:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so we have 70 extras here on set,\Nand then stunt people.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.02,0:25:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do digital versions of those,\Nso we can create the art for those 70
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.85,0:25:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to take them out to about 500.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.44,0:25:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then we've got the Outriders,\Nwhich are Thanos' beasts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.44,0:25:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's 10,000 of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.94,0:25:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SNARLING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.11,0:25:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}VICTORIA ALONSO:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}There was\Na lot of thinking into the texture,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.82,0:25:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what they felt like, what they\Nlooked like, what the teeth looked like.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.91,0:25:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to pose a real threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.08,0:26:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(GRUNTS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.24,0:26:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ALIENS YELPING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.96,0:26:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was she up there all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.58,0:26:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of our action is based around\Ncharacter decisions and moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.17,0:26:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Less punch/jab/cross/uppercut,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.51,0:26:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but it's more of the things{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.88,0:26:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of, "What are you going to remember\Nabout the character?"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.55,0:26:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Combination attacks working together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.34,0:26:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our goal, it's to give you\Nmoments and less choreography.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.64,0:26:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my favorite moments is\Nwhen Proxima tells Scarlet Witch...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.19,0:26:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll die alone. As will you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.94,0:26:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.27,0:26:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In a real,\Nreal moment of threat,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.40,0:26:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there's two other women there,\Nstanding by each other.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.28,0:26:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(YELLING){\c}{\fn\b0}\N- {\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(ALL GRUNTING){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.36,0:26:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really great to see\Nthat the audiences are embracing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.78,0:26:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}really strong female superheroines.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.21,0:26:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That is one of the biggest\Ncheer moments in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.67,0:26:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(YELLS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.34,0:26:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming into Infinity War,\Nadmittedly I was a little hesitant
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.68,0:27:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}because I just was so protective\Nof what myself and Taika sort of built.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.76,0:27:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, "Well, you know,\Nit's not the old Thor anymore,"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.18,0:27:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and Joe said,\N"No, no, we know."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.60,0:27:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And Anthony said,\N"Yeah, we get it,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.89,0:27:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"but we've got something\Ndifferent in mind as well."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.90,0:27:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And they were right.\NThey had a whole new version of it,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.77,0:27:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and one that was equally as enjoyable\Nas that last Thor film.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.99,0:27:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,New haircut?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.61,0:27:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice you've copied my beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.57,0:27:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.74,0:27:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Evans was a bit off,\Nbut I think mine sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.16,0:27:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(LAUGHTER){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.45,0:27:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In Atlanta, you get days like this,\Nwhich are amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.58,0:27:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that just resonate\Nwhat we're trying to get with Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.00,0:27:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And other days you'll get the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.05,0:27:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(THUNDER RUMBLING){\c}{\fn\b0}\N- {\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}MAN:{\c}{\fn\b0} Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.84,0:27:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}ALONSO:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}We had a lot\Nof different weather issues.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.22,0:27:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We had rain, sun, fog, cold, heat.\NWe had it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.43,0:27:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}TRAN:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}The weather was\None of the biggest challenges,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.73,0:27:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because it would just be pouring and\Nthere would be mud just sliding down
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.82,0:27:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as we're trying to get our talent\Nup to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.11,0:27:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And it was incredible.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.86,0:27:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}DeLEEUW:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}We do the best we can.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.95,0:28:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to cover actors for close-ups\Nand shoot the close-ups,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.20,0:28:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and then hopefully the next day we get\Na shot, you know, a day without rain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.62,0:28:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}TRAN:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}So when Thanos shows up,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.25,0:28:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we really wanted to make this\Nthe most powerful moment ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.71,0:28:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eyes up, stay sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.97,0:28:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The movie sort of keeps\Ntwisting at the end there
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.13,0:28:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in ways that you can't believe\Nthat it's going one step beyond,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.18,0:28:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and that the fate of\Nour characters{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.51,0:28:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fate of the universe\Nare still at play.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.23,0:28:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(SCREAMS){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.56,0:28:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In terms of our choices
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.81,0:28:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,about who Thanos would end up\Neradicating with his snap,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.90,0:28:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it was very story focused.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.65,0:28:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we pay off each individual\Ncharacter's storyline most profoundly?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.12,0:28:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}BUCKY:{\c}{\fn\b0} Steve?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.16,0:28:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The first person to go\Nis Bucky Barnes,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.45,0:28:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it's shot from\NCaptain America's perspective.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.91,0:28:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You know, we're watching Cap go through\Nthe experience of watching him go{\i0} away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.21,0:28:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We're watching Okoye,\Nwhose number one mission it is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.67,0:29:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in life is to protect the king.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.26,0:29:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She watches the king go\Nin front of her.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.18,0:29:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And to see those characters\Nreact in those situations
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.93,0:29:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is very powerful and resonant.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.85,0:29:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Groot! No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.81,0:29:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.98,0:29:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The blip-out sequence, we had gathered\Nthe whole entire talent there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.27,0:29:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,circled around our directors,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.48,0:29:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and basically revealed to them\Nthat morning of,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.32,0:29:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when they came on set, that\Nthat scene was happening,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.57,0:29:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that some of them were going to be,\Nyou know, disappearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.53,0:29:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The audience is so good\Nat predicting stories
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.62,0:29:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that even just the smallest clue can\Ntell them where the film is going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.79,0:29:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we worked really hard\Nto make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.54,0:29:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that none of the secrets\Nof the film leaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.21,0:29:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}TRAN:{\c}{\fn\b0} {\i1}This, by far, has been\Nthe most top-secret movie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.17,0:29:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out of all of the previous\N18 movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.80,0:29:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.05,0:29:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.43,0:29:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about as massive a production\Nas you can mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.02,0:29:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,6,000 crew members working on the movie,\Nspread all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.27,0:29:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This was so brutally massive\Nas a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.61,0:30:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's almost 3,000 shots\Nin the film,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.94,0:30:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and there's about\N2,900 visual effects shots.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.28,0:30:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a puzzle.\NIt's a difficult one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.07,0:30:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has ever assembled a cast\Nof this size and this caliber.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.28,0:30:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was a completely unique filmmaking\Nexperience for everybody involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.00,0:30:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}FEIGE:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}Of all the films we've made,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.42,0:30:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Infinity War will have\Nthe greatest repercussions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.42,0:30:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And, really, the only way\Nthis film could be made
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.55,0:30:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the hands\Nof Anthony and Joe Russo.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.76,0:30:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This production,\Nit has been a daunting task.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.60,0:30:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But we always knew\Nthat they're the people for the job.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.39,0:30:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine trying\Nto tackle such a huge task.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.27,0:30:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I had a lot of faith, not in just\NKevin Feige and the people of Marvel,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.06,0:30:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but the Russos. They're\Nbatting a thousand in my opinion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.19,0:30:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought on {\i1}Civil{\i0} War\Nthat we had 12 big cast members.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.74,0:30:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How are we going to deal\Nwith all these characters?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.28,0:30:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Compared to this movie,\Nwith over 30 cast.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.83,0:30:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the Russos prove themselves,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.16,0:30:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and they're able to integrate\Nall these characters together{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.66,0:30:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in a seamless manner.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.75,0:30:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- The energy's perfect.\N- Yeah, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.58,0:31:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides being incredibly smart,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.63,0:31:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the Russos are very trusting\Nand they are very kind to the crew.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.92,0:31:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}ANTHONY:{\c}{\fn\b0} Okay, everybody give it up\Nfor Geoff Haley!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.97,0:31:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.93,0:31:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Joe and Anthony want to create\Na relationship as quickly as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.43,0:31:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and that's what people\Nrespond to.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.23,0:31:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Last weekend were\Nthe Taurus World Stunt Awards,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.86,0:31:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the team from {\i1}Civil{\i0} War\Ndid very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.48,0:31:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&Hd900d9&\fnRockwell}(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE){\c}{\fn\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.74,0:31:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Russo brothers\Nhave brought some
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.36,0:31:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}extraordinary precision and complexity\Nto the Marvel Universe.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.99,0:31:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They are extraordinary technicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.00,0:31:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They are making\Nthe biggest movie of all time,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.42,0:31:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with the biggest movie\Nof all time right after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.54,0:31:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had a very strong\Ncollaboration
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.42,0:31:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with Markus and McFeely\Nover all four movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.30,0:31:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H808080&\fnRockwell}ANTHONY:{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\i1}It's a very organic process.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.76,0:31:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We sit there and we grab a character\Nand we start to tell a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.09,0:31:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We love this work so much\Nthat we want real fidelity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.72,0:31:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to what it is that we think\Nand believe about these characters,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.23,0:31:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and we really want that\Nto translate.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.73,0:32:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I think, when you get\Nto the end of these films,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.73,0:32:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you'll understand\Nour point of view on life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.10,0:32:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and our point of view\Nas filmmakers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.27,0:32:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So making these movies,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.52,0:32:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's been\Na very personal journey for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.05,0:32:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&H00ffff&\fnRockwell}Improved By: FidelPerez{\c}{\fn\b0}\N{\b1\c&Hffff00&\fnRockwell}Sub Upload Date: August 4, 2018{\c}{\fn\b0}